					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-706753#post-1869671</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-706753/scp-1435#post-1869671</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 12 Oct 2013 19:14:28 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Lexagon</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1411139</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>It's still not a realistic phrase even if it's the puppeteer. It's more likely to me that someone in severe, unexpected pain would utter a nonsensical vocalization (also known as a scream =), but you could get a nice effect by removing the &quot;Oh&quot; (which is the really-doesn't-sound-natural part) and making it &quot;It&#8230;hurts&quot; ala the last girl in the &quot;Raft&quot; segment from Creepshow. I think that might better convey the feeling of shock, incomprehensible pain and complete surprise someone might experience were their puppet to all of a sudden start to turn them into several meters of crushed bone and undifferentiated tissue.</p> <p>All very much my opinion of course. I love it the way it is, and I have to say, I found your &quot;spoiler&quot; explanation curiously satisfying =)</p> <p>+1</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
